

AIM:To Install Flutter and Dart SDK

DESCRIPTION:

Flutter is an open-source UI framework by Google for building native mobile, web, and desktop apps from a single codebase.
Dart is the programming language used to develop Flutter applications.
To run Flutter, we need to install both Flutter SDK and Dart SDK.

Procedure:
 Step 1: Install Git
•	Download Git from https://git-scm.com/downloads
•	Install and set the path variable.
Step 2: Download Flutter SDK
•	Go to https://flutter.dev/docs/get-strated/install
•	Download the Flutter SDK zip file.
•	Extract it to a location (Example: C:\src\flutter).
Step 3: Set Environment Variable
•	Open Environment Variables → Under User variables, click New →
Variable name: Path
Variable value: C:\src\flutter\bin
•	Click OK.
Step 4: Verify Installation
•	Open Command Prompt → Type:flutter –version
•	It will show the installed Flutter and Dart versions.
Step 5: Install Android Studio / VS Code
•	Install Android Studio or Visual Studio Code.
•	Add Flutter and Dart plugins from the Extensions Marketplace.
Step 6: Run Doctor Command
•	In terminal, type:flutter doctor
•	It checks the setup and shows if any dependencies are missing.
Output / Result:

After running flutter doctor, you’ll get output like this:
•	Doctor summary (to see all details, run flutter doctor -v):
•	[√] Flutter (Channel stable, 3.24.0, on Microsoft Windows [Version 10.0.26100])
•	[√] Android toolchain - develop for Android devices
•	[√] Chrome - develop for the web
•	[√] Visual Studio Code (version 1.91.2)
•	[√] Connected device (3 available)
•	
•	• no issues found 
